      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When glucose (Problem 19-51) is treated with NaBH<sub>4</sub>, reaction occurs to yield <i>sorbitol,</i> a polyalcohol commonly used as a food additive. Show how this reduction occurs.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb29XIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a65bd6b20e65ae89fcd1c2da845eb606be798ca7/OChem_19_EC_066.jpg\" alt=\"Alpha-glucose reacts with sodium borohydride and water to produce sorbitol, a six-carbon chain with one hydroxyl group on each carbon.\">",
